parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause the vehicle to slip or jerk, making it difficult to control.
symptoms: the vehicle jerks or slips when shifting gears
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission cooling system can cause the transmission to overheat, leading to premature wear and failure.
The failure of the U-joint can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power and control.
The failure of the wheel bearing can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause sudden and unexpected distraction, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also lead to unnecessary repair costs and vehicle downtime.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without any impact or collision
sudden and unexpected deployment of airbags
airbag warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear of the front brake rotors can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: grinding or squealing noises when applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine smoking can be a sign of a serious engine problem, which can lead to engine failure, decreased performance, and potentially cause accidents.
